## Structured Knowledge

<!-- Stable planning conventions, project constraints, and coordination-file patterns. -->
- For Data repo POC planning, prefer a balanced operational structure over either package abstractions or one giant script: roughly 4-5 code/config files under `scripts/` and `config/`, with prompts editable outside Python. Normal tests should use monkeypatch/test doubles and avoid live API calls, but user-facing runtime should use real LiteLLM only with no mock mode.
- The default live model for both generation and pruning decisions is `gemini/gemini-2.5-flash-lite`; load credentials from environment/`.env` without printing or inspecting secret values.
- Shared planning docs for this repo should live under `docs/`; generated datasets should go under `outputs/` and be gitignored unless the user explicitly wants to commit an artifact.
